verbose_text: Although the mechanisms of NFE2L2 signaling are not fully elucidated [XREF_BIBR], oxidative stress has a clear role in interacting with cysteine residues of Kelch like ECH associated protein 1 (Keap1), which decreases proteasomal degradation of NFE2L2 and thereby allows entry of NFE2L2 into the nucleus to induce transcription [XREF_BIBR - XREF_BIBR].
